distToSlice penalize complexity

Jason T. Serviss

2018-01-22

Set up functions. The basic strategy is to subtract e from the cost, with e representing the complexity of the model. We try various ranges of e including:

E1 = number of fractions > 0
E2 = (number of fractions > 0) / 2
E3 = (number of fractions > 0) / 10
E4 = (number of fractions > 0) / 100
E5 = (number of fractions > 0) / 1000

.makeSyntheticSlice <- function(
    cellTypes,
    fractions
){
    return(colSums(t(cellTypes) * fractions))
}

distToSliceNormE1 <- function(
    fractions,
    cellTypes,
    oneMultiplet,
    ...
){
    if(sum(fractions) == 0) {
        return(999999999)
    }
    normFractions <- fractions / sum(fractions)
    cellTypes <- cellTypes/mean(cellTypes)
    a = .makeSyntheticSlice(cellTypes, normFractions)
    a <- a/mean(a)
    k <- length(which(normFractions > 0))
    n <- length(fractions)
    (sum(abs((oneMultiplet - a) / (a+1)))) * (1 + ((k * 0.01) / n))
}

distToSliceNormE2 <- function(
    fractions,
    cellTypes,
    oneMultiplet,
    ...
){
    if(sum(fractions) == 0) {
        return(999999999)
    }
    normFractions <- fractions / sum(fractions)
    cellTypes <- cellTypes/mean(cellTypes)
    a = .makeSyntheticSlice(cellTypes, normFractions)
    a <- a/mean(a)
    k <- length(which(normFractions > 0))
    n <- length(fractions)
    (sum(abs((oneMultiplet - a) / (a+1)))) * (1 + ((k * 0.025) / n))
}

distToSliceNormE3 <- function(
    fractions,
    cellTypes,
    oneMultiplet,
    ...
){
    if(sum(fractions) == 0) {
        return(999999999)
    }
    normFractions <- fractions / sum(fractions)
    cellTypes <- cellTypes/mean(cellTypes)
    a = .makeSyntheticSlice(cellTypes, normFractions)
    a <- a/mean(a)
    k <- length(which(normFractions > 0))
    n <- length(fractions)
    (sum(abs((oneMultiplet - a) / (a+1)))) * (1 + ((k * 0.05) / n))
}

distToSliceNormE4 <- function(
    fractions,
    cellTypes,
    oneMultiplet,
    ...
){
    if(sum(fractions) == 0) {
        return(999999999)
    }
    normFractions <- fractions / sum(fractions)
    cellTypes <- cellTypes/mean(cellTypes)
    a = .makeSyntheticSlice(cellTypes, normFractions)
    a <- a/mean(a)
    k <- length(which(normFractions > 0))
    n <- length(fractions)
    (sum(abs((oneMultiplet - a) / (a+1)))) * (1 + ((k * 0.1) / n))
}

Calculate results.

calcResFull <- function(sObj, known, ec) {
  sObj %>% 
    checkResults(., known, edge.cutoff = ec) %>%
    mutate(cellsInWell = case_when(
      str_extract(multiplet, "..$") %in% c("01", "02", "03", "04") ~ 2L,
      str_extract(multiplet, "..$") %in% c("05", "06", "07", "08") ~ 3L,
      str_extract(multiplet, "..$") %in% c("09", "10", "11", "12") ~ 4L
  )) %>%
  select(multiplet, cellsInWell, data.detected:ACC)
}

res <- map(sObjs, ~calcResFull(.x, known, 0.2))

Show summary.

resSummary <- function(result) {
  result %>%
  group_by(cellsInWell) %>%
  summarize(
    meanTPR = mean(TPR, na.rm = TRUE),
    meanTNR = mean(TNR, na.rm = TRUE),
    meanACC = mean(ACC, na.rm = TRUE)
  )
}

Conclusion: With the sorted multiplet dataset we see few changes in the accuracy with the different “e” implemented cost functions. Although there is some variability in the results this would seem to stem from the non-deterministic nature of the optimization since no decernable pattern can be detected dependant on e. Below we utilize the “complexity” dataset to further evaluate these cost functions.

addComplexity <- function(uObj, k = 6, plot = TRUE) {

  #add complexity
  tsne <- getData(uObj, "tsne")
  km <- kmeans(tsne, k, iter.max = 100, nstart = 100)[[1]]
  km <- tibble(class = km, multiplet = names(km))
  
  #plot
  p <- c()
  if(plot) {
    p <- tsne %>%
    as.data.frame() %>%
    rownames_to_column(var = "multiplet") %>%
    as_tibble() %>%
    full_join(km, by = "multiplet") %>%
    mutate(class = parse_factor(class, levels = unique(class))) %>%
    ggplot() +
    geom_point(aes(x = V1, y = V2, colour = class))
  }
  
  #rename and add to spUnsupervised object
  newClass <- tibble(
    multiplet = rownames(tsne),
    classReal = getData(uObj, "classification")
  ) %>%
  full_join(km, by = "multiplet") %>%
  unite(combined, classReal, class) %>%
  pull(combined)
  
  classification(uObj) <- newClass
  return(list(uObj, p, km))
}

#rename
renameFnx <- function(sObj) {
  mat <- getData(sObj, "spSwarm")
  colnames(mat) <- gsub("(.*)..$", "\\1", colnames(mat))
  sObj@spSwarm <- mat
  return(sObj)
}

sObjsComplex <- map(sObjsComplex, ~renameFnx(.x))
